<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Strategic Implications of Tile Frequency</h2>

<p>The distribution isn't random — it mirrors English letter frequency. Here's what that means for strategy:</p>

<div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
  <p class="text-sm text-purple-300"><strong class="text-purple-400">Key Insight:</strong> With 12 E tiles in the bag, drawing multiple E's is common. Having 3+ vowels on your rack usually means exchanging tiles is worth more than forcing a weak play.</p>
</div>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Vowel management</strong> — 42 of 98 letter tiles are vowels. Expect roughly 3 vowels per draw of 7</li>
  <li><strong>S is gold</strong> — only 4 S tiles exist. Never waste an S for fewer than 8+ extra points</li>
  <li><strong>Blank tiles</strong> — worth 0 points but strategically priceless. Save for bingos (50-point bonus)</li>
  <li><strong>Power tiles</strong> — J, Q, X, Z exist as singles. If you see one played, it's gone forever</li>
  <li><strong>Tracking mid-game</strong> — by turn 10, roughly 70 tiles are visible. Count what's left to predict the endgame</li>
</ul>

